  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and involves multiple levels of legislation and regulation:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group standards\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing regulations\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial crime investigation units\n\n5. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional license revocation\n\n6. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Regular audits\n- Staff training programs\n- Technological monitoring tools\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
